HEADWORD: Argonaut
<hw>Ar"go*naut</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Argonauta</ets>, Gr. <?/; <?/ + <?/ sailor, <?/ ship. See
<er>Argo</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Any one of the legendary Greek
heroes who sailed with Jason, in the Argo, in quest of the Golden
Fleece.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A cephalopod of the genus
Argonauta.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of those who went to California in search of
gold shortly after it was discovered there in 1848.</def> <mark>[U.
S.]</mark> <rj><au>Bret Harte.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The ⟦ldquo⟧<qex>Argonauts</qex> of '49⟦rdquo⟧ were a strong,
self-reliant, generous body of men.</q> <rj><qau>D. S.
Jordan.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Argonauta</ent>⟦br⟧
